OL,3,CHuman error 'in general' caused fatal
OL,4,Cboat collision, defendant says
OL,6,FThe defendant told the court that the
OL,7,Fdecision to send Mr Sevash-Zade to
OL,8,Fbreakfast was an idea introduced by
OL,9,Fone of the other captains due to the
OL,10,F"commercial pressure of keeping the
OL,11,Fship on time".
OL,13,FMr Carr did, however, admit that it
OL,14,Fwas not a company policy.
OL,16,FCrown Advocate Matthew Malletois,
OL,17,Fprosecuting, later cross-examined Mr
OL,18,FCarr.
