OL,3,CHuman error 'in general' caused fatal
OL,4,Cboat collision, defendant says
OL,6,FCrown Advocate Malletois asked the
OL,7,Fdefendant if he agreed that the
OL,8,Fcollision was the result of human
OL,9,Ferror "in general", to which Mr Carr
OL,10,Fagreed.
OL,12,FFollowing this, Mr Carr also told the
OL,13,Fjury that the collision was "made
OL,14,Funavoidable by L'Ecume's actions".
OL,16,FWhen questioned by Crown Advocate
OL,17,FMalletois whether he thought he did
OL,18,Fnothing wrong, MrCarr said, "I didn't
OL,19,Fdo everything perfectly."
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G8/11
