OL,3,CHuman error 'in general' caused fatal
OL,4,Cboat collision, defendant says
OL,6,FMr Carr was also asked by the Crown
OL,7,FAdvocate whether he accepted that he
OL,8,F"made mistakes", to which the
OL,9,Fdefendant responded: "Things could've
OL,10,Fbeen done better".
OL,12,FWhile Mr Carr agreed that he had made
OL,13,Fmistakes on the bridge that morning,
OL,14,Fhe remained firm that the collision
OL,15,F"was caused by the L'Ecume's actions".
OL,17,FThe presiding judge on the case,
OL,18,FCommissioner Sir John Saunders, asked
OL,19,FMr Carr what he could have done better.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G9/11
