OL,3,CHuman error 'in general' caused fatal
OL,4,Cboat collision, defendant says
OL,6,FMr Carr explained that the danger of
OL,7,Fthe L'Ecume II could have been spotted
OL,8,Fearlier and action could have also
OL,9,Fbeen taken earlier.
OL,11,FThe defendant told the court that had
OL,12,Fhe taken evasive action earlier,
OL,13,F"hopefully the collision would have
OL,14,Fbeen avoided".
OL,16,FCrown Advocate Malletois asked Mr
OL,17,FCarr: "Do you now agree, a collision
OL,18,Fcould've been avoided if you had acted
OL,19,Fdifferently?".
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws        G10/11
